<paragraph blockId="31.[136,1451,410,581]" pageId="31" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,446,472]" pageId="31" pageNumber="242">Notes:—</emphasis>
The proliferous habit of this species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Schlechter" authorityYear="1912" box="[865,970,446,472]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pleurothallis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="31" pageNumber="242" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="frutex">
<emphasis box="[865,970,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="242">M. frutex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Luer &amp; R. Vasquez" box="[1030,1121,447,472]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="31" pageNumber="242" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gyas">
<emphasis box="[1030,1121,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="242">M. gyas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ortiz" authorityYear="1997" box="[1183,1332,447,472]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="31" pageNumber="242" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis box="[1183,1332,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="242">M. montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by bearing congested white flowers with a pubescent floral bract covering the base of the perianth and lateral sepals connate to near the middle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[136,1451,410,581]" box="[136,722,554,581]" pageId="31" pageNumber="242">
